UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. William Doxie THOMSON, Appellee. No. 7112. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 17, 1933. John R. Layng, U. S. Atty., and Lewis M. Andrews, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal. David Spaulding, of West Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for the respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
